        "import numpy as np\n",
        "import cvxpy as cp\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Basic linear-algebra helpers\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def kron(*args):\n",
        "    out = np.array([[1.0]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for a in args:\n",
        "        out = np.kron(out, a)\n",
        "    return out\n",
        "\n",
        "def dagger(a):\n",
        "    return np.conjugate(a.T)\n",
        "\n",
        "def partial_trace(rho, dims, keep):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Partial trace for density matrix rho with subsystem dimensions 'dims'.\n",
        "    keep: list of subsystem indices to keep (0-based).\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    dims = list(dims)\n",
        "    n = len(dims)\n",
        "    keep = list(keep)\n",
        "    trace_over = [i for i in range(n) if i not in keep]\n",
        "\n",
        "    reshaped = rho.reshape(dims + dims)\n",
        "    for t in sorted(trace_over, reverse=True):\n",
        "        reshaped = np.trace(reshaped, axis1=t, axis2=t+n)\n",
        "        dims.pop(t)\n",
        "    d_keep = int(np.prod(dims)) if dims else 1\n",
        "    return reshaped.reshape(d_keep, d_keep)\n",
        "\n",
        "def von_neumann_entropy(rho, eps=1e-12):\n",
        "    rho = 0.5 * (rho + dagger(rho))  # ensure Hermitian\n",
        "    w = np.linalg.eigvalsh(rho)\n",
        "    w = np.clip(np.real(w), 0.0, 1.0)\n",
        "    w = w[w > eps]\n",
        "    return float(-np.sum(w * np.log(w)))\n",
        "\n",
        "def mutual_information(rho_ab, dims=(2,2)):\n",
        "    rho_a = partial_trace(rho_ab, list(dims), keep=[0])\n",
        "    rho_b = partial_trace(rho_ab, list(dims), keep=[1])\n",
        "    return von_neumann_entropy(rho_a) + von_neumann_entropy(rho_b) - von_neumann_entropy(rho_ab)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Pauli matrices\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "I2 = np.eye(2, dtype=complex)\n",
        "X = np.array([[0, 1],[1, 0]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "Y = np.array([[0, -1j],[1j, 0]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "Z = np.array([[1, 0],[0, -1]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Channels via Kraus operators\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def apply_kraus(rho, kraus_ops):\n",
        "    out = np.zeros_like(rho, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for K in kraus_ops:\n",
        "        out += K @ rho @ dagger(K)\n",
        "    return out\n",
        "\n",
        "def depolarizing_kraus(p):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Single-qubit depolarizing channel:\n",
        "    D_p(rho) = (1-p)rho + (p/3)(X rho X + Y rho Y + Z rho Z)\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    p = float(p)\n",
        "    k0 = np.sqrt(max(0.0, 1.0 - p)) * I2\n",
        "    kx = np.sqrt(max(0.0, p/3.0)) * X\n",
        "    ky = np.sqrt(max(0.0, p/3.0)) * Y\n",
        "    kz = np.sqrt(max(0.0, p/3.0)) * Z\n",
        "    return [k0, kx, ky, kz]\n",
        "\n",
        "def unitary_kraus(U):\n",
        "    return [U]\n",
        "\n",
        "def channel_kraus_product(kraus_A, kraus_B):\n",
        "    return [kron(Ka, Kb) for Ka in kraus_A for Kb in kraus_B]\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Build the toy channel E_{theta,p}\n",
        "#   E_{theta,p}(rho) = (D_p  D_p)( U(theta) rho U(theta)^\\dagger )\n",
        "# with U(theta)=exp(-i theta XX)\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def U_xx(theta):\n",
        "    XX = kron(X, X)\n",
        "    return np.cos(theta) * np.eye(4, dtype=complex) - 1j * np.sin(theta) * XX\n",
        "\n",
        "def E_theta_p_kraus(theta, p):\n",
        "    U = U_xx(theta)\n",
        "    K_unit = unitary_kraus(U)\n",
        "    K_noise = channel_kraus_product(depolarizing_kraus(p), depolarizing_kraus(p))\n",
        "    return [Kn @ Ku for Ku in K_unit for Kn in K_noise]\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Choi matrix and diamond norm SDP\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def choi_from_kraus(kraus_ops, d_in, d_out):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Choi matrix J = sum_{ij} Phi(|i><j|)  |i><j|\n",
        "    using computational basis. Returns (d_out*d_in) x (d_out*d_in).\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    J = np.zeros((d_out*d_in, d_out*d_in), dtype=complex)\n",
        "    basis = np.eye(d_in, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for i in range(d_in):\n",
        "        for j in range(d_in):\n",
        "            Eij = np.outer(basis[:, i], basis[:, j].conj())  # |i><j|\n",
        "            Phi_Eij = apply_kraus(Eij, kraus_ops)            # d_out x d_out\n",
        "            J += np.kron(Phi_Eij, Eij)\n",
        "    return J\n",
        "\n",
        "def choi_of_difference(kraus_E, kraus_F, d_in, d_out):\n",
        "    J_E = choi_from_kraus(kraus_E, d_in, d_out)\n",
        "    J_F = choi_from_kraus(kraus_F, d_in, d_out)\n",
        "    return J_E - J_F\n",
        "\n",
        "def diamond_norm_from_choi(J, d_in, d_out, solver=None, verbose=False):\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    Watrous-style SDP (primal) for Hermiticity-preserving maps:\n",
        "      max Re Tr(J X)\n",
        "      s.t.  [ I_out  rho    X\n",
        "             X^            I_out  rho ]  >= 0\n",
        "            rho >= 0, Tr(rho)=1\n",
        "\n",
        "    Here J is the Choi matrix of the linear map Phi (not necessarily CP),\n",
        "    with dimensions (d_out*d_in) x (d_out*d_in).\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    dimX = d_out * d_in\n",
        "    rho = cp.Variable((d_in, d_in), complex=True)\n",
        "    Xvar = cp.Variable((dimX, dimX), complex=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "    Iout = np.eye(d_out, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    I_rho = cp.kron(Iout, rho)\n",
        "\n",
        "    block = cp.bmat([[I_rho, Xvar],\n",
        "                     [Xvar.H, I_rho]])\n",
        "\n",
        "    constraints = [\n",
        "        block >> 0,\n",
        "        rho >> 0,\n",
        "        cp.trace(rho) == 1\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    objective = cp.Maximize(cp.real(cp.trace(J @ Xvar)))\n",
        "    prob = cp.Problem(objective, constraints)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if solver is None:\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            prob.solve(solver=cp.SCS, verbose=verbose, eps=1e-5)\n",
        "        except Exception:\n",
        "            prob.solve(solver=cp.CVXOPT, verbose=verbose)\n",
        "    else:\n",
        "        prob.solve(solver=solver, verbose=verbose)\n",
        "\n",
        "    val = prob.value\n",
        "    if val is None:\n",
        "        raise RuntimeError(\"Diamond norm SDP did not return a value. Try a different solver or settings.\")\n",
        "    return float(val)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# AOI (operational) toy:\n",
        "#   admissible class = LO (product channels) approximated by\n",
        "#   C_q = (D_q  D_q)   (no entangling unitary)\n",
        "# and we estimate: delta(theta,p) = min_q || E_{theta,p} - C_q ||_diamond\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def C_q_kraus(q):\n",
        "    return channel_kraus_product(depolarizing_kraus(q), depolarizing_kraus(q))\n",
        "\n",
        "def estimate_delta_min_over_q(theta, p, q_grid, solver=None):\n",
        "    kraus_E = E_theta_p_kraus(theta, p)\n",
        "    best = None\n",
        "    best_q = None\n",
        "    d_in = d_out = 4\n",
        "\n",
        "    for q in q_grid:\n",
        "        kraus_C = C_q_kraus(q)\n",
        "        Jdiff = choi_of_difference(kraus_E, kraus_C, d_in, d_out)\n",
        "        dn = diamond_norm_from_choi(Jdiff, d_in, d_out, solver=solver, verbose=False)\n",
        "        if (best is None) or (dn < best):\n",
        "            best = dn\n",
        "            best_q = q\n",
        "    return best, best_q\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Run a small sweep and plot\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def run_toy_sweep(\n",
        "    thetas=np.linspace(0, np.pi/4, 7),\n",
        "    ps=np.linspace(0.0, 0.6, 7),\n",
        "    q_grid=np.linspace(0.0, 0.9, 10),\n",
        "    solver=None\n",
        "):\n",
        "    # fixed input state |00><00|\n",
        "    ket00 = np.array([1,0,0,0], dtype=complex)\n",
        "    rho0 = np.outer(ket00, ket00.conj())\n",
        "\n",
        "    I_vals = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "    delta_vals = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "    q_best_vals = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        for j, p in enumerate(ps):\n",
        "            # output state and mutual information\n",
        "            rho_out = apply_kraus(rho0, E_theta_p_kraus(th, p))\n",
        "            I_vals[i, j] = mutual_information(rho_out, dims=(2,2))\n",
        "\n",
        "            # AOI distance estimate (min over q in product depolarizing family)\n",
        "            d_est, q_best = estimate_delta_min_over_q(th, p, q_grid, solver=solver)\n",
        "            delta_vals[i, j] = d_est\n",
        "            q_best_vals[i, j] = q_best\n",
        "\n",
        "            print(f\"theta={th:.3f}, p={p:.3f}  ->  I={I_vals[i,j]:.4f},  delta~{d_est:.4f} (q*={q_best:.2f})\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return thetas, ps, I_vals, delta_vals, q_best_vals\n",
        "\n",
        "# Execute a quick run (keep grids modest; diamond SDP is the expensive part)\n",
        "thetas, ps, I_vals, delta_vals, q_best_vals = run_toy_sweep(\n",
        "    thetas=np.linspace(0, np.pi/4, 6),\n",
        "    ps=np.linspace(0.0, 0.5, 6),\n",
        "    q_grid=np.linspace(0.0, 0.9, 10),\n",
        "    solver=cp.SCS\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot mutual information surface (as heatmap)\n",
        "plt.figure()\n",
        "plt.imshow(I_vals.T, origin=\"lower\", aspect=\"auto\",\n",
        "           extent=[thetas[0], thetas[-1], ps[0], ps[-1]])\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"theta\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"p\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Mutual Information I(A:B) for output of E_{theta,p} on |00>\")\n",
        "plt.colorbar()\n",
        "plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# Plot estimated AOI distance delta(theta,p) (as heatmap)\n",
        "plt.figure()\n",
        "plt.imshow(delta_vals.T, origin=\"lower\", aspect=\"auto\",\n",
        "           extent=[thetas[0], thetas[-1], ps[0], ps[-1]])\n",
        "plt.xlabel(\"theta\")\n",
        "plt.ylabel(\"p\")\n",
        "plt.title(\"Estimated AOI distance  delta(theta,p) = min_q ||E_{theta,p} - (D_qD_q)||_\")\n",
        "plt.colorbar()\n",
        "plt.show()"
      ]
    },

        "    return von_neumann_entropy(rho_a) + von_neumann_entropy(rho_b) - von_neumann_entropy(rho_ab)\n",
        "\n",

        "# Pauli matrices + some standard 1q unitaries\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "I2 = np.eye(2, dtype=complex)\n",
        "X = np.array([[0, 1], [1, 0]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "Y = np.array([[0, -1j], [1j, 0]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "Z = np.array([[1, 0], [0, -1]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "H = (1/np.sqrt(2)) * np.array([[1, 1], [1, -1]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "S = np.array([[1, 0], [0, 1j]], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "def unitary_set_small():\n",
        "    # Small discrete set; expand later if you like\n",
        "    U = []\n",
        "    U.append(I2)\n",
        "    U.append(X); U.append(Y); U.append(Z)\n",
        "    U.append(H)\n",
        "    U.append(S)\n",
        "    U.append(H @ S)\n",
        "    U.append(S @ H)\n",
        "    U.append(H @ Z)   # = XH up to phase (still fine)\n",
        "    return U\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Channels via Kraus operators\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def apply_kraus(rho, kraus_ops):\n",
        "    out = np.zeros_like(rho, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for K in kraus_ops:\n",
        "        out += K @ rho @ dagger(K)\n",
        "    return out\n",

        "\n",

        "    return [U]\n",
        "\n",
        "def channel_kraus_product(kraus_A, kraus_B):\n",
        "    return [kron(Ka, Kb) for Ka in kraus_A for Kb in kraus_B]\n",
        "\n",
        "def compose_kraus(kraus_after, kraus_before):\n",
        "    # (after)  (before)\n",
        "    return [Ka @ Kb for Kb in kraus_before for Ka in kraus_after]\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Toy physical channel E_{theta,p}\n",
        "#   E_{theta,p}(rho) = (D_p  D_p)( U(theta) rho U(theta)^\\dagger )\n",
        "# with U(theta)=exp(-i theta XX)\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def U_xx(theta):\n",
        "    XX = kron(X, X)\n",
        "    return np.cos(theta) * np.eye(4, dtype=complex) - 1j * np.sin(theta) * XX\n",

        "def E_theta_p_kraus(theta, p):\n",
        "    U = U_xx(theta)\n",
        "    K_unit = unitary_kraus(U)\n",
        "    K_noise = channel_kraus_product(depolarizing_kraus(p), depolarizing_kraus(p))\n",
        "    return compose_kraus(K_noise, K_unit)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Choi matrix and diamond norm SDP\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def choi_from_kraus(kraus_ops, d_in, d_out):\n",
        "    J = np.zeros((d_out*d_in, d_out*d_in), dtype=complex)\n",
        "    basis = np.eye(d_in, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    for i in range(d_in):\n",
        "        for j in range(d_in):\n",
        "            Eij = np.outer(basis[:, i], basis[:, j].conj())\n",
        "            Phi_Eij = apply_kraus(Eij, kraus_ops)\n",
        "            J += np.kron(Phi_Eij, Eij)\n",
        "    return J\n",
        "\n",
        "def diamond_norm_from_choi(J, d_in, d_out, solver=None, verbose=False):\n",
        "    dimX = d_out * d_in\n",
        "    rho = cp.Variable((d_in, d_in), complex=True)\n",
        "    Xvar = cp.Variable((dimX, dimX), complex=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "    Iout = np.eye(d_out, dtype=complex)\n",
        "    I_rho = cp.kron(Iout, rho)\n",
        "\n",
        "    block = cp.bmat([[I_rho, Xvar],\n",
        "                     [Xvar.H, I_rho]])\n",
        "\n",
        "    constraints = [\n",
        "        block >> 0,\n",
        "        rho >> 0,\n",
        "        cp.trace(rho) == 1\n",
        "    ]\n",
        "\n",
        "    objective = cp.Maximize(cp.real(cp.trace(J @ Xvar)))\n",
        "    prob = cp.Problem(objective, constraints)\n",
        "\n",
        "    if solver is None:\n",
        "        solver = cp.SCS\n",
        "\n",
        "    prob.solve(solver=solver, verbose=verbose, eps=1e-5)\n",
        "    if prob.value is None:\n",
        "        raise RuntimeError(\"Diamond norm SDP returned None; try a different solver or relax eps.\")\n",
        "    return float(prob.value)\n",
        "\n",
        "def diamond_distance_between_channels(kraus_E, kraus_F, d_in=4, d_out=4, solver=None):\n",
        "    J_E = choi_from_kraus(kraus_E, d_in, d_out)\n",
        "    J_F = choi_from_kraus(kraus_F, d_in, d_out)\n",
        "    return diamond_norm_from_choi(J_E - J_F, d_in, d_out, solver=solver, verbose=False)\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Admissible family (fast, still LO):\n",
        "#   C = (U_A  D_{qA})  (U_B  D_{qB})\n",
        "# (You can swap order if you want; keep fixed for comparability.)\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def local_channel_kraus(U, q):\n",
        "    return compose_kraus(unitary_kraus(U), depolarizing_kraus(q))\n",
        "\n",
        "def admissible_kraus(Ua, qa, Ub, qb):\n",
        "    Ka = local_channel_kraus(Ua, qa)\n",
        "    Kb = local_channel_kraus(Ub, qb)\n",
        "    return channel_kraus_product(Ka, Kb)\n",
        "\n",
        "def estimate_delta_over_admissible_family(theta, p, q_grid, U_set, solver=None):\n",
        "    kraus_E = E_theta_p_kraus(theta, p)\n",
        "    best = None\n",
        "    arg = None\n",
        "    for qa in q_grid:\n",
        "        for qb in q_grid:\n",
        "            for Ua in U_set:\n",
        "                for Ub in U_set:\n",
        "                    kraus_C = admissible_kraus(Ua, qa, Ub, qb)\n",
        "                    dn = diamond_distance_between_channels(kraus_E, kraus_C, solver=solver)\n",
        "                    if (best is None) or (dn < best):\n",
        "                        best = dn\n",
        "                        arg = (qa, qb, Ua, Ub)\n",
        "    return best, arg\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Two inputs: |00> and |++>\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def ket0():\n",
        "    return np.array([1, 0], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "def ket1():\n",
        "    return np.array([0, 1], dtype=complex)\n",
        "\n",
        "def ket_plus():\n",
        "    return (1/np.sqrt(2)) * (ket0() + ket1())\n",
        "\n",
        "def rho_from_ket(ket):\n",
        "    return np.outer(ket, ket.conj())\n",
        "\n",
        "def build_inputs():\n",
        "    ket00 = kron(ket0(), ket0())\n",
        "    ketpp = kron(ket_plus(), ket_plus())\n",
        "    return {\n",
        "        \"|00>\": rho_from_ket(ket00),\n",
        "        \"|++>\": rho_from_ket(ketpp),\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Run sweep + plots\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "def run_sweep(\n",
        "    thetas,\n",
        "    ps,\n",
        "    q_grid,\n",
        "    solver=cp.SCS,\n",
        "    U_set=None,\n",
        "    print_rows=True\n",
        "):\n",
        "    if U_set is None:\n",
        "        U_set = unitary_set_small()\n",
        "\n",
        "    inputs = build_inputs()\n",
        "\n",
        "    I_maps = {name: np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps))) for name in inputs.keys()}\n",
        "    delta_map = np.zeros((len(thetas), len(ps)))\n",
        "    arg_map = [[None for _ in range(len(ps))] for _ in range(len(thetas))]\n",
        "\n",
        "    for i, th in enumerate(thetas):\n",
        "        for j, p in enumerate(ps):\n",
        "            kraus_E = E_theta_p_kraus(th, p)\n",
        "\n",
        "            for name, rho0 in inputs.items():\n",
        "                rho_out = apply_kraus(rho0, kraus_E)\n",
        "                I_maps[name][i, j] = mutual_information(rho_out, dims=(2, 2))\n",
        "\n",
        "            d_est, arg = estimate_delta_over_admissible_family(th, p, q_grid, U_set, solver=solver)\n",
        "            delta_map[i, j] = d_est\n",
        "            arg_map[i][j] = arg\n",
        "\n",
        "            if print_rows:\n",
        "                qa, qb, Ua, Ub = arg\n",
        "                print(f\"theta={th:.3f}, p={p:.3f}  ->  \"\n",
        "                      f\"I00={I_maps['|00>'][i,j]:.4f},  Ipp={I_maps['|++>'][i,j]:.4f},  \"\n",
        "                      f\"delta~{d_est:.4f} (qa={qa:.2f}, qb={qb:.2f})\")\n",
        "\n",
        "    return I_maps, delta_map, arg_map\n",
        "\n",
        "def heatmap(data, thetas, ps, title):\n",
        "    plt.figure()\n",
        "    plt.imshow(\n",
        "        data.T,\n",
        "        origin=\"lower\",\n",
        "        aspect=\"auto\",\n",
        "        extent=[thetas[0], thetas[-1], ps[0], ps[-1]]\n",
        "    )\n",
        "    plt.xlabel(\"theta\")\n",
        "    plt.ylabel(\"p\")\n",
        "    plt.title(title)\n",
        "    plt.colorbar()\n",
        "    plt.show()\n",
        "\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "# Parameters (tune for speed/accuracy)\n",
        "# ----------------------------\n",
        "thetas = np.linspace(0, np.pi/4, 6)\n",
        "ps = np.linspace(0.0, 0.5, 6)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Refined q-grid compared to before (still manageable).\n",
        "# Warning: delta estimation cost scales ~ O(len(q)^2 * len(U)^2) SDP solves per (theta,p).\n",
        "q_grid = np.linspace(0.0, 0.9, 13)\n",
        "\n",
        "# Small unitary set; increase only after you see stable qualitative behaviour.\n",
        "U_set = unitary_set_small()\n",
        "\n",
        "I_maps, delta_map, arg_map = run_sweep(\n",
        "    thetas=thetas,\n",
        "    ps=ps,\n",
        "    q_grid=q_grid,\n",
        "    solver=cp.SCS,\n",
        "    U_set=U_set,\n",
        "    print_rows=True\n",
        ")\n",
        "\n",
        "heatmap(I_maps[\"|00>\"], thetas, ps, \"Mutual Information I(A:B) for output of E_{theta,p} on |00>\")\n",
        "heatmap(I_maps[\"|++>\"], thetas, ps, \"Mutual Information I(A:B) for output of E_{theta,p} on |++>\")\n",
        "heatmap(delta_map, thetas, ps, \"Estimated AOI distance delta(theta,p) to LO family (UD_q)(UD_q)\")"
      ],
